ArifC"><div class="sc-d56bc236-5 BJZni"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" width="20px" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" data-cy="icon-aeon-save" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M17 3H7c-1.1 0-1.99.9-1.99 2L5 21l7-3 7 3V5c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 15l-5-2.18L7 18V5h10v13z"></path></svg><span class="sc-d56bc236-4 gKlMxC">Save</span></div><p class="sc-d56bc236-0 sc-d56bc236-3 iOJnhy eIqCxs">essay</p><p class="sc-d56bc236-0 sc-d56bc236-2 iOJnhy llXHdp">Astronomy</p></div><p class="sc-d56bc236-10 tdBWn">Alien life is no joke</p><p class="sc-d56bc236-11 hYbLtW">Not long ago the search for extraterrestrials was considered laughable nonsense. Today, it’s serious and scientific</p><p class="sc-d56bc236-0 sc-d56bc236-12 iOJnhy dFhhBp">Adam Frank</p></div><div class="sc-d56bc236-6 kQroYe"></div></div></a><a href="/essays/what-thucydides-really-thought-about-historical-analogies"><div class="sc-d56bc236-9 eCvrmh"><div type="essay" class="sc-82db9615-2 kSWDpk"><img alt="A marble bust of Thucydides is shown on a page from an old book. The opposite page is blank." loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 960px) 45vw, (max-width: 1440px) 30vw, 430px" srcSet="https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/d68a83b8-7f41-402a-97e2-c5ce2aeebc9f/essay-final-2g3pw9p.jpg?width=256&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 256w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/d68a83b8-7f41-402a-97e2-c5ce2aeebc9f/essay-final-2g3pw9p.jpg?width=384&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 384w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/d68a83b8-7f41-402a-97e2-c5ce2aeebc9f/essay-final-2g3pw9p.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 640w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/d68a83b8-7f41-402a-97e2-c5ce2aeebc9f/essay-final-2g3pw9p.jpg?width=750&amp;quality=75&amp;format=auto 750w, https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/d68a83b8-7f41-402a-97e2-